t:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:2px;color:#A100FF;margin-bottom:8px">Level 2 · Advanced (after Level 1)</div><div style="font-size:.88rem;font-weight:700;color:#001228;margin-bottom:8px">Leapfrog with digital / AI / IoT</div><ul class="blist" style="font-size:.8rem"><li>Intelligent Store (Vusion, AI scheduling)</li><li>E-commerce integration (FR)</li><li>Disruptive models (uberized)</li></ul><div style="margin-top:10px;font-size:.7rem;color:rgba(0,18,40,.5);font-style:italic">CAPEX-dependent. High return ceiling.</div></div></div><div class="g3"><div class="step-card"><div class="step-ico">🔍</div><div class="step-title">The WHATs first</div><div class="step-desc">Map the complete E2E of the store process and identify the domains where real value exists to unlock. Without rushing to the how — and without defaulting to technology before the basics are fixed.</div></div><div class="step-card"><div class="step-ico">🤖</div><div class="step-title">AI where it adds value, not by default</div><div class="step-desc">Agentic AI makes sense in scheduling, inventory and shelf monitoring. Not in organizational decisions, team structure or labor negotiations. Level 1 first, Level 2 on solid ground.</div></div><div class="step-card"><div class="step-ico">📏</div><div class="step-title">Measurement from day 1</div><div class="step-desc">Define the KPI framework before entering. Establish baseline. Measure at midpoint (week 4). Value must be a data point, not a PowerPoint estimate.</div></div></div><div class="div"></div><div class="ibox ibox-blue"><div class="ibox-title">🗺️ The 4 RFP work-streams — our answer</div><div class="ibox-body"><ul class="blist"><li><strong>① Fine understanding of levers</strong> → E2E map of all value pools (in-store + upstream), prioritized by impact and maturity</li><li><strong>② Internal (FR/ES) + external benchmark</strong> → Activity-level benchmark at seconds/box × product family — not ratios, but gestures</li><li><strong>③ Costed recommendations by horizon</strong> → Quick wins (6m) · Operating-model transformation (12m) · Intelligent Store (24m)</li><li><strong>④ Store-segment operationalization plan</strong> → Differentiated by store format, with Carrefour-side accompaniment and implementation support</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="inner-1-casos" class="inner-panel"><p class="slide-sub">Three projects that define our value proposition in store operations. Click to see the impact.</p><div class="ref-grid"><div class="ref-card"><div class="ref-inner"><div class="ref-front"><div><div class="ref-tag">Grocery Retailer · Mexico, Chile &amp; Argentina</div><div class="ref-icon">🛒</div><div class="ref-company">Large-scale grocery retailer</div><div class="ref-headline">Bottom-up workforce dimensioning with task-demand operating model — from sales-history planning to real task-demand modelling, at industrial scale</div></div><div class="ref-front-bottom"><div class="ref-tags"><span class="ref-tag-sm">WFM</span><span class="ref-tag-sm">Store ops</span></div><span class="ref-link">See detail →</span></div></div><div class="ref-back"><div class="ref-challenge">Workforce planned from historical sales, not real task volume. No internal benchmark; high variability across stores of the same format.</div><div class="ref-role-label">Our role</div><ul class="ref-bullets"><li>Full L4 process mapping across all store departments (receiving → floor → checkout → back office)</li><li>Task-demand operating model: task volume × time standard = real headcount demand by shift</li><li>Scheduling redesign to align staffing with actual demand curves</li><li>Pilot: 9 express/proximity format (equiv. Carrefour Express) + 9 convenience format (BM / Día type) → rolled out to 104 convenience + 38 express/proximity formats · then Chile &amp; Argentina</li></ul><hr class="ref-divider"><div class="ref-impact-label">Impact</div><div class="ref-impact-big"><div class="ref-impact-num">+20–30%</div><div class="ref-impact-num-sub">Labour productivity improvement</div></div><div class="ref-impact-pills"><div class="ref-impact-pill">10–17%<br>structural efficiency</div><div class="ref-impact-pill">3,000+<br>stores transformed</div></div><div class="ref-back-close">← Close</div></div></div></div><div class="ref-card"><div class="ref-inner"><div class="ref-front"><div><div class="ref-tag">Large retail · Spain</div><div class="ref-icon">🏬</div><div class="ref-company">European multi-format retailer</div><div class="ref-headline">E2E store operations reinvention: ESL, Click &amp; Collect, WFM and omnichannel fulfillment to unlock EBITDA</div></div><div class="ref-front-bottom"><div class="ref-tags"><span class="ref-tag-sm">Store ops</span><span class="ref-tag-sm">ESL</span><span class="ref-tag-sm">WFM</span></div><span class="ref-link">See detail →</span></div></div><div class="ref-back"><div class="ref-challenge">Leading European retailer under margin pressure — needed to unlock productivity in execution, e-commerce fulfillment and inventory simultaneously.</div><div class="ref-role-label">Our role</div><ul class="ref-bullets"><li>E2E operational diagnostic: value pool mapping across all store processes</li><li>ESL rollout — 400,000+ labour hours redeployed annually to higher-value tasks</li><li>Click &amp; Collect redesign: smart lockers replacing manual handoff (NPS 47→65)</li><li>Order preparation: process redesign reducing lead time from days to hours</li><li>WFM model aligned with real traffic and demand data</li></ul><hr class="ref-divider"><div class="ref-impact-label">Impact</div><div class="ref-impact-big"><div class="ref-impact-num">&gt;€40M</div><div class="ref-impact-num-sub">Value unlocked across the store network</div></div><div class="ref-impact-pills"><div class="ref-impact-pill">NPS 47→65<br>Click &amp; Collect</div><div class="ref-impact-pill">400k+ hrs<br>redeployed / year</div></div><div class="ref-back-close">← Close</div></div></div></div><div class="ref-card"><div class="ref-inner"><div class="ref-front"><div><div class="ref-tag">Grocery Retailer · Uruguay</div><div class="ref-icon">🏪</div><div class="ref-company">Multi-format grocery chains</div><div class="ref-headline">Efficiency programme based on task-demand operating model — 25-store pilot scaled to full network</div></div><div class="ref-front-bottom"><div class="ref-tags"><span class="ref-tag-sm">Store ops</span><span class="ref-tag-sm">WFM</span></div><span class="ref-link">See detail →</span></div></div><div class="ref-back"><div class="ref-challenge">Two grocery chains with labour at 16.9% of sales — pressure to improve efficiency without service cuts or arbitrary headcount reductions.</div><div class="ref-role-label">Our role</div><ul class="ref-bullets"><li>Analysis (6w): full E2E baseline of both chains across all store processes</li><li>Design (8w): task-demand operating model and operating routines adapted to 2 store formats</li><li>Pilot (6w): live deployment in 25 stores with embedded on-site coaching</li><li>Sustainability model handed over to HQ for network-wide scaling</li></ul><hr class="ref-divider"><div class="ref-impact-label">Impact</div><div class="ref-impact-big"><div class="ref-impact-num">11.2%</div><div class="ref-impact-num-sub">Workforce efficiency captured · 459 FTEs</div></div><div class="ref-impact-pills"><div class="ref-impact-pill">338M $UY<br>annual savings</div><div class="ref-impact-pill">Labour cost<br>16.9%→15.4%</div></div><div class="ref-back-close">← Close</div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="inner-1-diferencia" class="inner-panel"><div class="g3"><div class="step-card"><div class="step-ico">🏪</div><div class="step-title">We know the hypermarket inside out</div><div class="step-desc">We don't arrive with a generic framework. We've led transformations in real hypermarkets, with unions (France), with legacy systems and with store teams that keep selling while changing.</div></div><div class="step-card"><div class="step-ico">📊</div><div class="step-title">We measure before, during and after</div><div class="step-desc">KPI framework defined before entry. Baseline in week 1. Midpoint in week 4. Audited result in week 8. Value is not a hypothesis; it's a number.</div></div><div class="step-card"><div class="step-ico">🔄</div><div class="step-title">Back office included</div><div class="step-desc">The analysis is not limited to the sales floor. It includes administration, reporting, HR management, supply processes and coordination with head office. The complete E2E.</div></div></div><div class="div"></div><div class="ibox ibox-dark"><div class="ibox-title">🎯 Our differentiating stance</div><div class="ibox-body">Real benchmarking comes from having been in these stores, not from external databases. Our advantage is not the methodology (everyone has one); it's the real operational knowledge of the hypermarket format in Europe.</div></div></div></section>

